cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes an architecture for an Air-Ground Integrated Vehicular Network (AGIVEN) and investigates the problem of multi-resource provisioning in AGIVEN slicing. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of content pushing and caching in AGIVEN and derives analytical results for the optimal communication-cache resource trading. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the provision of location-based map and popularity-based content services in AGIVEN, which may involve multimedia content. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a service-oriented network slicing approach to efficiently manage the multi-dimensional heterogeneous resources in AGIVEN. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the guaranteed quality of service (QoS) for each slice in AGIVEN and derives the minimal RSU transmission rate to meet the average delay requirements of each slice, which may involve control systems.
